# 🚀 feature request

### Relevant Package
This feature request is for @angular/forms

### Description
form.reset() only set values to null so if my form have a FormArray with 3 items `ctrl=[toto,tata,tutu]`,  form reset will set data to null: `ctrl=[null,null,null]` but expected behavior should be `ctrl=[]` ( and this is what clear does)

### Describe the solution you'd like
a `form.clear()` or a `form.resetAndClear()`  that set length to zero for all sub FormArrays 


### Describe alternatives you've considered
Here is how I do it now:
```
Object.keys(this.controls).forEach((key: string) => {
  const abstractControl = this.controls[key];
    if (abstractControl instanceof FormArray) {
      abstractControl.clear();
    }
});
```

