### Is this a regression?
Yes, the previous version in which this bug was not present was: v7.x.x

### Description
If you have a `@font-face` in your styles and serve/build with a base-href your urls will be incorrect.

Tested with both SCSS and LESS both fail in v8. Testing in v7 LESS passes.

## 🔬 Minimal Reproduction
**Angular 7**
`ng new angular7Test` with LESS
`ng serve --prod --base-href=/app/`

Add this too app.component.less
```
// Set antialiasing as default
html {
  -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale; // Fix for Mozilla
  font-family: sans-serif;
}

// Mixin to simplify inclusion of local web fonts
.AddFontFace(@FontFileName, @FontFriendlyName, @FontLocation, @FontWeight, @FontStyle) {
  font-family: @FontFriendlyName;
  src: url("@{FontLocation}@{FontFileName}.eot");
  src: url("@{FontLocation}@{FontFileName}.eot?#iefix")
      format("embedded-opentype"),
    url("@{FontLocation}@{FontFileName}.woff") format("woff"),
    //url('@{FontLocation}@{FontFileName}.woff2') format('woff2'),
      url("@{FontLocation}@{FontFileName}.ttf") format("truetype"),
    url("@{FontLocation}@{FontFileName}.svg#@{FontFriendlyName}") format("svg");
  font-weight: @FontWeight;
  font-style: @FontStyle;
}

// Location of all fonts
@font-files-location: "/assets/shared/fonts/";

// Univers Regular (Used as Bold)
@font-face {
  .AddFontFace(
    "universbq-regular-webfont",
    "UniversBQ",
    "@{font-files-location}",
    bold,
    normal
  );
}

* {
  font-family: "UniversBQ";
}
```

You will see the fonts import with `/app/` prepended.

**Angular 8**
`ng new angular8Test` with LESS
`ng serve --prod --base-href=/app/`

Same steps above but the fonts will fail with 404 as they are looking for `/assets/...` and not `/app/assets/...`

